g the whole span from the basics to dedusting, absorption, adsorption and redox processes. The didactic concept of the work is to attract students with a ‘learning by doing’ strategy. We discuss the problems, the solver strategies and the solvers. The problem solver proposals address a multitude of pollution control technologies. The work is a compact off-gas purification guide for practitioners and students by presenting basics as well as numerous applications with many examples and problems with solutions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAbgasreinigung. 4aAbluftreinigung. 4aAbsorption. 4aAdsorption. 4aLuftreinhaltung. 4aLuftverschmutzung. 7aSCIENCE / Environmental Science (see also Chemistry / Environmental).2bisacsh  a.  aAbsorption.  aAdsorption.  aAir Pollution.  aAir Retension.  aExhaust Gas Cleaning.  aWaste Air-Purification.1 aLux, Susanne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSiebenhofer, Matthäus, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2023 Englishz978311131923008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2023z9783111318660oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831107640000 cprintz978311076390440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076392840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110763928423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110763928/original  a978-3-11-11757